### Never use rec:

```nix
# ❌ rec { a = 1; b = a + 1; }
# ✅
let a = 1; in { inherit a; b = a + 1; }
```

### Never destructure with `with`:

```nix
# ❌ args: with args; stdenv.mkDerivation { ... }
# ✅ { stdenv, fetchurl, ... }: stdenv.mkDerivation { ... }
```

## Best Practice Checklist

```markdown
- [x] No `with`
- [x] Explicit destructuring
- [x] nixfmt formatting
- [x] Namespaced options
- [x] Prefer let-in over rec
- [x] Platform guards for Linux/Darwin-specific deps
- [x] No hardcoded `/home/` paths — use `config.home.homeDirectory`
- [x] Multi-system support (all 4 platforms unless explicit constraint)
- [x] lib.mkIf/mkMerge for conditions
- [x] Assert for validation
```

## Validation

```bash
nix flake check           # Lint/test flake
nixfmt .                  # Format code
nix eval .#packages.x86_64-linux.default
nix flake show            # Show outputs
```

